  "prompt": "My WhatsApp web is not working. I'm using the Chrome browser on my Windows 8.1 laptop, and the internet speed is decently good. I opened web.whatsapp.com and the QR code doesn't load up at all. It just keeps going round and round. How can I fix this?",
  "response": "Here are several troubleshooting steps to fix WhatsApp Web issues:\n\n1. Basic Checks\n- Refresh the webpage\n- Clear browser cache and cookies\n- Restart Chrome browser\n- Restart your laptop\n\n2. Browser-specific Solutions\n- Update Chrome to the latest version\n- Disable Chrome extensions temporarily\n- Try incognito/private browsing mode\n- Clear browser data completely\n\n3. Internet & Network\n- Check your internet connection\n- Try a different network/Wi-Fi\n- Disable VPN if you're using one\n- Restart your router/modem\n\n4. WhatsApp App Settings\n- Ensure WhatsApp on your phone is updated\n- Check \"Linked Devices\" in WhatsApp mobile app\n- Log out and log back into WhatsApp Web\n\n5. Technical Fixes\n- Disable hardware acceleration in Chrome\n- Check system date and time settings\n- Try a different browser (Firefox, Edge)\n- Reinstall Chrome\n\n6. Advanced Troubleshooting\n- Scan for malware\n- Check antivirus/firewall settings\n- Reset Chrome settings\n- Reinstall WhatsApp on your phone\n\nIf none of these work, contact WhatsApp support or check their official help resources.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
